2. From the following table, write a SQL query to compute the experience of all the managers. Return employee ID, employee name, job name, joining date, and experience. 

select emp_id, emp_name, job_name, hire_date, (DATE_PART('year', CURRENT_DATE)-DATE_PART('year', hire_date)) as "Experience"
from employees
WHERE emp_id IN
    (SELECT manager_id
     FROM employees)
order by (DATE_PART('year', CURRENT_DATE)-DATE_PART('year', hire_date)) desc
;
